  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the angel said unto him, gird thyself,.... He slept in his inner garment loose about him; wherefore the angel bids him gird it up with his girdle, and prepare to walk out after him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and bind on thy sandals; which were a sort of shoes that covered only the soles of the feet, and were fastened to the leg, with strings: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and so he did; he did not ask any question, or the reason of these orders; he did not dispute the matter, but at once obeyed: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and he saith unto him, cast thy garment about thee; meaning his upper garment, or cloak, which lay by him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and follow me; suggesting hereby, that he should take care of him, and show him his way, and bring him safe out of the prison. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and follow me; suggesting hereby, that he should take care of him, and show him his way, and bring him safe out of the prison. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
